content.detailedDescription: I was driving northbound on u.S. 31, just south of berrien springs, at about 4 p.M. to my left (west), i observed a very bright light about 40 feet above an open field. it was absolutely still (not even really "hovering"). it was about 50 to 60 feet west of me. i initially thought it was a private aircraft on approach to a small airport that lay nearby in berrien springs. however, as i kept glancing at the light while driving, i realized it was not moving. then i thought i might be looking at the sun, only to see that the sun was further southwest of me & the light. i kept glancing at it, and wondering what it was. it made no sound, no move. it was not connected to a light pole or any other mechanical apparatus. then, i glanced again and realized the light had vanished. nothing remained in the air. the entire event lasted about 3 minutes. i still don't know what i saw. the field was empty and there were no trees, or anything else it could have been connected to.
content.summary: Bright, circular light in the air; no aircraft or light apparatus observed

content.detailedDescription:
In back yard sitting on patio facing west. wife sitting across from me facing east. 10 pm. sky clear and lots of stars. if i wasn't appreciating the beauty of the night sky, i would never have seen this thing. it was very stealthy, its movement gave it away as it blocked out the stars as it passed underneath them giving it away. it approached from the n.W. and passed nearly directly overhead and moved out of view headed straight s.E. lost sight as it went over top our house. moved quickly and did not alter speed. as it went overhead, i could see dimly-lit pot lots under the wings of this chevron - shaped object that appeared solid and black.The lights created a dim glow on the sides of the pots they appeared to be recessed in. there was four to five lights under each wing.
not a sound was made.
sighting lasted 5 seconds.
was sitting with my wife and pointed it out to her but she couldn't see it in time before it went over the house. she was facing east across the table from me so she didn't have enough time to see what i was looking at.
felt excited and at the same time re-assured that i wasn't the only one that has seen this as i've seen the exact thing depicted in re-creations on ufo documentaries over the years.
i've seen objects before on occasion, increased over the last five years in this area, always a bright orange light. but this was the first time i've actually seen a solid object and could see its shape.
very sneaky and the odds of anyone seeing this would be rare if they weren't looking up at the right time and place and detected the stars getting blocked out just for a second.
content.summary: Solid, dark chevron-shape object with dim circular pot-lights evenly spaced underneath, four or five under each wing. traveled very quickly in straight line.

content.detailedDescription: I am a skywatcher in upstate ny the hudson valley area and i was conducting a live skywatch on youtube. we all noticed these 3 objects or possibly ! object go across the screen. my footage is recorded through a security dvr system and i was able to find the segment which we all had seen during the live stream. event was only a few seconds in duration and i was using my night vision equipment. there was no sound during this event.

content.detailedDescription: im on a family vacation here in clear water florida . we rented a beach front with patio. on the 9/13/2015  me and my fiancé have seen something amazing . for the first time in my life i saw a ufo or better said ufos . they were over the ocean traveling from north to south . sky was clear full of stars . it was not an airplane or anything i could identify . especially flying so fast and changing formation before disappearing. it was 3 orange/red lights and as i told my fiancé to look . it switched the formation from 3 triangle formation to a 4-5 light straight bar before our eyes.. and then  it disappeared in the sky . the speed it was traveling and changing formation blew my mind . this all happened within 5-8 seconds somewhere around 11pm over the ocean .
content.summary: Triangle formed into a straight bar like shape . the rear light moved forward lined up and released another orb.That lined up also .

content.detailedDescription: My mom, dad, boyfriend, and i were night fishing on the coast of rodanthe, north carolina. we noticed a few brights lights up in the sky, almost a mile off the coast to the south east. they were close, then spread out a bit and hovered, then just vanished. we all saw it. there was no ship in the ocean and it did not look like a flare. the lights hovered, then just vanished. they did not fall or descend. it was about 9:45 - 10 pm. we were night fishing so it was dark and the lights were easy to spot. i did not know what it was when i first saw it. i have been skeptical about ufos, but after what i saw i am a believer.
content.summary: Lights glowing over ocean. then disappeared.

content.detailedDescription:
Location of sighting: maylandsea
date of sighting: july 1968
time: appx 10:30 pm

witness statement:	i have never reported this before as i didn’t want to be categorised with the usual ufo spotter. i was on my way to school, i was going in late, i got to the top of mayland hill when i heard the trees rustling, this was odd as there was no wind at all, i glanced to the side and was shocked to see a disc shaped object hovering app 10ft above the ground. it was not very large, i would estimate 30ft in diameter. it made no sound at all, but the trees near it were moving as if a moderate wind were blowing. the most amazing thing about it was the underside, i was about 200ft from it and could see it very clearly. in the centre of the base was a large clear dome and around the edge of the underside were 8 smaller clear domes. the centre one was full of a, what i can only describe as liquid marble. it was a combination of reds that slowly swirled around, it looked just like when you stir red paint, you get the marble effect before it mixes in to on shade, but this fluid kept it’s individual shades. 4 of the small domes had the same red fluid in whilst the other 4 had the same type of fluid, but it was orange instead of red. i was only 12 and unfortunately after a couple of minuets i got spooked ( ufo’s weren’t really heard about back then) i jumped on my bike and peddled home as fast as i could. the road i lived in was unmade so you had to walk down it, it was then that i saw another weird craft in the sky in the direction of bradwell. it was long and thin with a drooping nose, it had 4 smaller craft moving around it. when i got home i did drawings of what i had seen. when my father got home he did his nut about me not going to school and said my ufo story was made up and not to tell anyone about it, but when he saw the picture of the long thin craft that i’d drawn he was a bit shocked. he was an aerospace engineer, he opened his briefcase and got out some top secret pictures. they were of concord! it was exactly the same as what i had drawn especially the drooping nose and the large tailplane. it seems that it was on a secret test flight and the small craft around it was an escort fighter jets.
i thought, even back then, that it was a strange coincidence that our first supersonic aircraft was passing only a few miles from where i saw the ufo. i know a lot of people won’t believe this story, but i swear it is true. the thing that really made it stick in my memory was the marbled liquid in the clear domes, it was mesmerising to look at. it was the only ufo i have ever seen, even though over the years i have spent countless amounts of time looking at the sky.
content.summary: Underside  had large central dome & 8 smaller domes around it.

content.detailedDescription: Observing morning sky. venus was visible and quite brilliant. over a period of several minutes bright orbs seemed to emit around venus. some sent straight out in several directions. a few split into several directions. and one or two seemed to circle venus prior to  shooting off into space. none appeared to move toward earth.

content.detailedDescription: It was 2:30am , i let my dog out in the backyard to do his business , as i walk out the backdoor onto the covered patio i look up to my right because i thought i saw movement in the clouds,it was very large and black , no lights, no noise and gliding below the clouds ,i could not make out a shape because it was so big , i thought i was seeing things , but then this v shaped object kind of rose up and mad a slight turn from south to southwest , it appeared the v shaped object was an escort for the larger object , i stepped out from under the patio to get a better look but unless you are within 500 ft or so i don't think you can see it, i just want to know if anyone else saw this , i could not sleep after i saw this.
content.summary: Observed very large black object with a v shaped object escorting it

content.detailedDescription:
I opened the curtains in the living room as i was going to bed at around 10:30pm and noticed a white patch in the sky that moved.  i put out the lights and watched the sky.  i saw a number of light patches in the sky.  

it was cloudy and my first thought was that it was some kind of light show being projected from below, maybe an event or concert or something.  the lights moved from various positions in the sky into a central point and out again, their speed reinforced my thoughts that they were a projection from below as it was implausible that anything else would be capable of moving at the apparent speed that they moved.  as i watched i became conscious of a very large area of sky that seemed to be slightly brighter than the rest positioned at the point where the white lights kept sweeping back to.  it was very faint just a hint of greenish light barely perceptible in the clouds.  it was only visible for a few minutes and seemed to slowly fade out completely, sometimes being barely detectable and sometimes not.  i didn't see it any more after this, although the white lights continued for a long time.

after 10 minutes or so i decided to go outside for a better view.  there was no sound or other sensation. the lights continued to sweep across the sky back into their central formation and out again to various random positions.  sometimes there were only two visible, sometimes up to five or six.  occasionally they came together to form a line and seemed to have beams of light from the front of the formation - it reminded me of the crown on the statue of liberty. then they would resume their random movement.

this continued and i tried to take a video on my phone but it just came out black.  i then tried taking pictures and managed to get a few images with blurry faint patches of light in them.  i just took pictures sequentially hoping to get something useful.  because the lights were moving only a few came out very faintly in the pictures, most pictures showed nothing.

this had been going on now for over an hour and it occurred to me that it couldn't be a show or event.  there was no sound, no distant music and it was nearing midnight on a sunday.  i became worried and called my ex-wife on the phone.  she lives about two miles away; and asked her if she could see anything from her place.  she could not, but stayed on the phone and talked about what i could see as it continued.  i then went and looked out from the front of the house and at the rest of the sky to see if there was any activity anywhere else.  there was none.  only the area of sky extending away between the north and north west had these strange lights.

i was still on the phone to my ex and she suggested that we call the police to explain what was going on and enquire as to whether they knew of any events or if anyone else had seen anything.  i agreed and she called them as i continued to watch the sky.

she called me back to say that the police had said that there were no events that they knew of and that there had been no other reports of these lights.  they said they would investigate and possibly send an officer to my house.  i never had a visit from them and heard nothing more.  i imagine they thought it a hoax.

by now it was nearing 12:30 and i was very tired.  i went to bed, but could not sleep.  around 1:30 i got up and looked out of the back upstairs window.  the lights had moved much further away and there seemed to only be three or four of them.  they had moved maybe a mile to the north but seemed quite bright.  i tried taking some more pictures with my phone and some were quite successful this time.  the lights were closer to the horizon, just visible above the roof line.  the weather was deteriorating and it was raining now.  the lights became fainter, and harder to see, presumably because of the rain.

by now i was tired, worried and frankly frightened by the imagined consequences of what i had seen.  i went to bed and slept on and off for the rest of the night.  when i awoke, which seemed to be every hour or so i went and looked out of the window but i didn't see any more lights.

a coincidence?

in the morning i noticed that my rain gauge wasn't working.  i monitor and log the weather as a hobby and looked to see how much rain we had had in the night.  the display said 4700mm of rain; clearly an impossibility.

inside the sensor is a small "spoon" which tips over when it fills with rain. it takes 0.5mm of rain for one "tip" operation.  there is a small magnet in the end of the spoon which passes a hall-effect sensor as the spoon tips, thus recording the amount. it appears that this sensor had recorded over 9400 magnetic operations overnight.  also the sensor was no longer working, sending random data to the weather logger.  

i have a second 'commercially bought' weather station which has a similar rain gauge.  i keep two as a backup and to compare data between them and derive an average.  the rain gauge for the second station which is of similar design is mounted on the roof.  that too had recorded over 4000mm (8000 + ) operations overnight, but still appears to be operational.

all this was on sunday night.  it is now tuesday morning.  i set up a 'security' camera last night to cover the same area of sky.  last night was clear and i looked out regularly.  there was nothing out of the ordinary to see last night.  i don't know if the camera is sensitive enough to record anything anyway but i have left it out.  today it is raining so i expect there to be cloud cover tonight. the same conditions as sunday. time will tell.

i was going to upload my pictures but as there are around 30 of them it didn't seem that practical.  contact me if you want copies and i'll upload them.  they are about 900kb each.

i decided to upload just the last few that show the lights best.  these are from about 1:30 when the lights were further away.  you can see them just above the roofs.
content.summary: Varying number (2-8) light patches in sky. random flight path but regularly coming together. 11pm to 2am. seen through cloud.

content.detailedDescription: On the morning of the 15th of september i was star gazing  with my telescope. i occasionally would stop and look around because there were many meteorites that morning. the first object i saw was moving north and south at an extremely fast rate and also was pulsating. in between pulses it was very hard to see. approximately 6 or 7 minutes later i saw another one. about 5 minutes after that i saw the third one the first three were all the same. all three were moving north to south extremely fast covering the width of the sky in approximately one and a half to two seconds. shortly after the third one maybe 2 3 4 minutes i saw the pair. the pair were moving north and south and were travelling faster than the first three but as they were moving they were moving side to side and slowing down and speeding up very quickly. about two-thirds across the sky one of them stopped and the other went so fast that it made a blinding streak of light vertically. after that i thought it was over but about 15 minutes later i saw three of them return from south to north one after the other none were together. i assume it was the same ones but i suppose it could have been different ones but i knew it was the same type of object because of the erratic way they were speeding up and slowing down.
content.summary: Saw 5 objects the first 3 were singles and the last 2 were together all were moving extremely fast covered the width of the sky in about 2 seconds

content.detailedDescription: My father called me to the back yard as something caught his eye on the tree line. watched 3 metallic objects hover and form different formations. essentially splitting apart from 3 to around 10 craft  hovering at roughly the same altitude the whole 1 hour and a half, when a cigar shaped craft flew in from the east over the ocean at unknown speeds. i live by patrick afb so i know the speeds of civilian and military aircraft neither of which was this craft. to seemingly dissipate/disappear before the eyes knocked on neighbors doors to verify sighting. crafts seemed to be in airspace above where the launch the space shuttle and other commercial spacecraft. had video evidence but contrast on iphone 1 was horrible as the craft where to far away to see clearly
content.summary: Metallic balls hovering in strange formations. as well as cigar shaped mothership

content.detailedDescription: I was on night duty doing security from 12am-8am five nights a week starting sunday midnight turning monday to friday morning 8am when my week of shifts were done..I spent all my nights outside watching over the property so my eyes an ears open to what ever went on..On sept, 23rd. 2010 after the last of the workers left for home i set the alarm an went an did my rounds before parking sitting an waiting an watching like always when i stood outside the security car to have a cigerate to observe the night sky full of stars ..Full moon above facing south of me i noticed to my right westward a bright white glowing circle slowly heading my way eastward...As it got closer lights started pulsating from all around it making no noise as it went overhead heading east...Like i looked at the full moon acouple times quick to try an guess the size of it an to me i'd say alittle over 3 times biggers then the full moon but maybe thats because it was low..I did light a cigerate just asecond or two before i seen an by the time it went by me my cigerate was done without taking a puff of it..Had to take alook see if i still had my shoes on after that..The maintance man who cuts grass showed up pushing a lawnmower along the buildings an yelled out to him did you see that but he said no an asked what ..He just laughed an said it was prolly a airplane ...Noway i spent years outside i no this was no airplane.

content.detailedDescription:
I was flying a frontier flight from co to dallas fw.  the flight departed co at about 4:50 pm.  we had arrived at our cruising altitude about 10 minutes before seeing the object.  i had taken several pictures of the clouds and was continuing to observe them when i saw an odd shaped object leaving a strange looking vapor trail.  my phone was on the tray so i grabbed it and snapped a few pictures.  the object was moving from east to west when i first saw it.  it was also dropping in altitude.  as it started to pass beyond my view (we were moving east while the object was moving west) it made a sudden turn downward and appeared to make a roll-like maneuver to assume a west to east path.  at this point it was moving close to parallel with our flight.  it held this path for about twenty seconds before suddenly disappearing.

when looking at the attached photos note they are in sequence.  they have not been altered in any way.  the object appears to be small - the pictures are taken with an iphone 5.  the object is in every image, once you find it you'll be able to track it in the photos.

image 5005:  fairly centered in the image.  this is the first photo. the object is moving at about a 30 degree angle towards ground on a western track.

image 5006: right hand side of the photo.  the object made a sharp turn straight downward.  there are two vapor trails visible.  this was taken as the object made it's downward turn and roll changing flight direction from west to east.

image 5007, 5008, and 5009:  the image can be seen almost center of the photo.  it tracked almost the same speed as our flight for about 20 seconds before suddenly disappearing.
content.summary: Observed object while flying out of denver, co.  moving e to w, dove hard, rolled, and began a w to e path before disappearing.

content.detailedDescription: I was taking photos of the super moon on 08/28/2015.  i noticed a small black dot on one of the photos.  i know it isn't dust or dirt on the lens,  it is in only one of many photos of the moon i took that night.  i also made sure there was no aircraft in the area when i was shooting.  i originally passed it off and a random event,  but then i read a report that someone else had photographed a pyramid shaped craft over the moon that very same night.  i figured i would share this with you guys and see if it is anything to you.  please feel free to enlarge these photos,  one is an original shot,  and the other is a cropped image.  tha k you for your time.
content.summary: Ufo in front of the super moon.

content.detailedDescription:
I was being driven back to leicester by my family three of us were in the car my father was driving my mother in the back we were in a citroen c4 picasso which has a large sunroof. as we drove south passing junction 24a of the m1 we noticed an aircraft on its approach to east midlands air port the sky was still light and had broken cloud. as the aircraft landed i also noticed a small dot on the cloud it was several miles away. as it approached my father said "there is a helicopter too." 
as the object approached it did not appear to be a helicopter there was no rotor there were no lights windows or markings. it was rectangular with a fin pointing toward the ground. it appeared very black i could not easily see its three dimensional shape i did not believe it was a ufo i thought it might be a bird, a balloon or a black bag but its shape remained consistent it gave the impression of being a jet black stone. it was traveling faster than the on coming traffic. it flew in a straight line and its slight appeared stable without any hovering. there were no exhaust emissions and no noise louder than the car.  
i leant forward in my seat and watched it go overhead it at an altitude of 300ft and appeared to be traveling north i watched it through the sunroof my mother complained that she couldn't turn around to see it. it appeared to be a dot once more and i lost sight of it. at the time i didn't believe it was a ufo it became stranger as i thought about it and had no explanation for it. i regret not taking a picture or following it. 
a few days later i had a dream about the incident where the object appeared to be a telescopic inspection basket for changing streetlights. i heard my self saying in the dream "oh its only one of those."
content.summary: Black object flying north above the m1 from east midlands airport uk

content.detailedDescription:
This past friday evening my girlfriend and i stayed at a resort in sw colorado, room 317. the following morning at 6am i got up and went to the window and was looking to the ne and this circular
object was about 1000 feet above this mesa or short mountian top, it looked like a silver sphere with a dark area in the center. it looked white and silver at the same time. i stared at it for a couple of minutes before i called out to my girlfriend to grab her camera phone and come take a picture before the sunrise. the sun had'nt risen yet and was about to break the top of the mesa. the object had slowly started geting further away ascending at a 60 degree angle there abouts, but seemed like it was very slowly going up. around 657am or so the sun popped out and i couldnt see it anymore. i was not sure at first that it was not a star, when i realized it was actually hovering right behind the resort and not a star thats when i snapped and thought, oh crap a ufo honey get the camera.
content.summary: I woke up to a strange circular object in the sky, hovering above a mesa till the sunrise then i lost sight of it

content.detailedDescription: ~ 9:10 pm september 14, 2015: ~ two hours after sunset i was out on my 3rd floor balcony, flying my quad copter, enjoying the lights on it (red, white and blue)very nice.  flew it straight out about 75 feet, directed it up to around 75-100 feet above ground and swooooosh, in my peripheral vision to slight right, i saw a tear drop shape object pointed end first head swiftly to the west ( more right )of my southern view. freeked me out a little because it was illuminated by what i will have to say ambient light from the neighborhood and streetlights etc. the sky at the time was sparsely partly cloudy, low humidity, with fluffy clouds so there was visible blue ( but dark ) night sky and clear visible stars, jet planes etc. winds were calm. finished flying the quad and, wow, i was thinking, was this ufo stationary and just observing us, me, someone?  did they get startled because my quad out there? was too funny-weird to not take this incident "freak-me-out" serious. brought the copter back in and got goose bumps. :d p.S. my guesstimate of it's speed will be ~250-400 mph and possibly more as it began to fade from sight at 50% to the right. i first caught perisight of it at around 20 degrees to my right and swooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooosh!
content.summary: All of a sudden, like it known it was seen or panic, swoooooosh straight line.

content.detailedDescription:
I was outside my camper and i was checking out the stars as they were starting to appear in the night sky.  my attention was drawn to an object that had flared up (possibly reflecting sunlight?). at first i believed the object to be a satellite as i frequently observe satellites in the night sky in this remote area.  after the object finished flaring up, i observed it as a very tiny pinpoint sized light.  as i watched it, i noticed that it was making very quick, subtle changes in direction.  i thought this might just be my eyes playing tricks on me.  all of a sudden the object made a very fast change in its direction and covered a great distance.  i knew then it was not my eyes playing tricks on me.  i observed many more of these sudden directional changes as the object zig-zagged all around.  the object then proceeded to head in a direction that took it north (with smaller zig-zags) until it disappeared over the trees.  this was followed by two more objects that exhibited the same type of behavior.  after these sightings, there was quite a bit of airline traffic coming into and leaving the (rochester?) airport.  this was followed by an unusually high number of satellites (very straight, quick, well-defined path).  as i stated, i often sit out at night watching satellites go overhead and this is the first time in my life that i have ever seen anything as unusual as this.

- the lights with the very fast changes in direction and speed were very, very dim.  i would guess they were very far away.
content.summary: Tiny star size objects abruptly changing path. first object flared up.

content.detailedDescription: I was laying in my bed thinking about the day ahead of me and what time i have to get up. i reached over to the table side and looked at my phone to see what time it was and how much sleep i would not get. it was 12:23am. i turned on my left side put a pillow between my legs and put the blankets over me to snuggle in for the night. i could not sleep. all of a sudden i felt drugged. like when you have a procedure. i got loopy and my body was limp and the next thing i knew i was being carried/held in a standing position through a neighborhood like setting, not sure if it was my neighborhood but i was going along slightly above the trees. it felt like a giant object had a hold of most of my torso, but my head and feet were free. i was not going upwards just straight head at such a speed that the lights i seen were a blur. i felt the cool wind all over me and my hair was flying back ,like if you stuck your head out of car window but at such a high speed, that i have not experienced. i felt and said to my self what the hell is happening but at the same time is was very relaxing and peaceful. the next thing i knew i  was thrown down on my bed on my back. i felt a dominant being over me. i could not move but was trying to. i felt scared and the peaceful feeling was instantly gone. it was holding me down but not in just one spot. it was over my chest arms and legs. i could move my head feet and hands but nothing else. i felt a warm being on me. my first thought that came to mind was that a man broke into the house and was trying to harm me. i then knew it was not a man. i could not see it. i felt like something was put into my eyes that made me have blurred vision and that seemed like black smoke. i could not cry out for my son.I kept blinking at the same time to adjust my eyes but couldn't focus them. i knew it was not a human, but it was something else. it had a powerful sense, very dominate feeling. it was warm and very heavy. it felt almost like hair but it was not hairy, it was a blurred black presence. i could not breathe or move my torso. i tired crying out for my son but because i was constricted i could not. i was thinking i got to get free. i thought i was going to die. the remote control was laying next to me and i thought i could grab it and throw it through the window to set off the house alarm so my son could come help me. i could not do that either. i heard something saying do not move. it was not a voice, more like a mental message. i heard strange noises like a sound from an mri and other noises, that i cant describe by writing. i said it hurts stop. i told myself to get free and with all my strength i lifted out of it. at that moment it was gone. i instantly felt pain in my lower back/spine area and stomach. burning pain. my throat was extremely dry. i noticed that i was laying on my back with all the blankets and pillows off me. i was laying there like i was being held down. i was to afraid to get up from the bed. it felt like hours had went by. i reached over and called my son on his cell phone to come downstairs to my room. he did. i still could not get my vision back, my throat was dry and in a few minutes after my vision cleared the pain went away. my throat was still dry and i drank some water that was next to my bed. i got up from the bed and felt exhausted and looked into the mirror. my hair was all back just if i had blow dried it that way. i told my son what happened and we talked about it for awhile. we checked the doors, they were locked and the alarm was on. he kept the lights on for me. i was afraid because i knew it would not matter if the lights were on or off. i knew this happened to me and there was nothing i could do to stop it.  i just asked him to sleep in the living room which is next to my room for the night. i did end up going to sleep and woke up and went to work. i told my friend about the experience. as i told her about it, the time frame was off. i looked at my phone to check the time. i thought i called my son about 130am,because it felt like a long time but in fact it was only 7 minutes that this all occurred in. according to my cell phone it was 1230am that i called my son to come downstairs.  i am telling my story to further help me understand this experience. i do not take drugs, i am a professional health care provider, a respected member of the community and an overall normal person. this is crazy to me and i cant find a rational explanation. i do know i was not sleeping nor am i making this experience up to get any type of attention. i am hoping for any feedback, is there anyone out there that this has happened to? any response will be helpful.
content.summary: I felt that i was visited by a being that was not human. i was taken from my bed and then brought back . a being hled/forced me down. i had pain and visual disturbances.
